I think that society is on a whole new level when it comes to being able to say whatever the hell they want to. Using Crowder as an example, people often make the excuse that, "He's a comedian, it's a joke!" But, I find that it almost never comes off as a joke or funny and he's just being an asshole.

I'm not sure if this change in policy is good or bad, but at the end of the day, just be kind to each other... It's never a good thing to be on the receiving end of hurtful, and sometimes completely untrue, statements.
